# Always check out text files with LF line endings, regardless of the
# platform's git config (e.g. Windows' common core.autocrlf=true default).
# This isn't just cosmetic: gofmt considers a CRLF-terminated file
# "unformatted" regardless of its actual content, so without this, `gofmt
# -l .` flags every single .go file on a Windows checkout -- not real style
# violations, just line-ending translation. Bit us on the first Windows CI
# run (see .github/workflows/ci.yml).
* text=auto eol=lf

*.go text eol=lf
go.mod text eol=lf
go.sum text eol=lf
